      <description>Biography I am computer scientist interested in emergent phenomena in complex systems, networks, segregation dynamics, urban transportation as well as a graph and data driven quantification of these phenomena.
I&#39;m currently a PhD Candidate in Mathematical Sciences at Queen Mary University of London with supervision by Vincenzo Nicosia. My research lies on quantifying the heterogeneity of spatially-embedded systems through random walks on graphs with particular interest on socio-economic segregation.
